Cone representation

Cone Finder app allows you to represent cones in different ways. You can change marks itself, make distinction between those who were marked manually and automatically and even represent them as Voronoi Diagram polygons.
Table of Contents
Cone mark type Mark options Additional Features Voronoi Diagram

Cone mark type

There are 3 mark type available:
  • Dot
  • Circle
  • Cross

Mark options

There are 3 mark options available:
  • Show manual + automatically detected cones
  • Show only manual detected cones
  • Show only automatically detected cones

Additional Features

Also, you can highlight the automatically detected cones when you present all cones together by option Highlight Autodetected Cones
And Cone marks can be turned off by option Show Marked Locations

Voronoi Diagram

Cones can be also represented as Voronoi Diagram patches. You can show it by Voronoi Diagram option.
Voronoi Diagram can represent different info. Available types are:
  • Empty - shows not filled Voronoi patches.
  • Cone Area - each Voronoi patch is filled by the color based on the area of the patch.
  • Number of Neighbors - each Voronoi patch is filled by the color based on the number of neighboring patches (patches that sharing the side of polygon)
